lls. Should I use a real JDBC driver since Doobie core doesn't include H2?\\\"},{\\\"type\\\":\\\"summary_text\\\",\\\"text\\\":\\\"**Exploring test dependency options**\\\\n\\\\nI’m considering adding a test dependency since the rules don’t forbid it. It might be beneficial to create a better public API using `fromDriverManager` with the driver \\\\\\\"org.h2.Driver\\\\\\\" and the URL \\\\\\\"jdbc:h2:mem:...\\\\\\\". I could also add `testImplementation com.h2database:h2`, but my focus should be on the active class. H2’s native image compatibility intrigues me, especially concerning metadata and dynamic class loading. It might be simpler to implement our own `java.sql.Driver` as a test source. I wonder if `Class.forName` needs metadata for the test driver class to succeed.\\\"},{\\\"type\\\":\\\"summary_text\\\",\\\"text\\\":\\\"**Clarifying the driver initialization process**\\\\n\\\\nI can explicitly reference the class to ensure it gets included, but the method call still needs to be dynamic. I need to make sure that `DriverManager` can return a connection if the driver is registered successfully. To avoid requiring a real connection, I could use a custom driver that's registered via the class's static initialization. However, using Scala's companion object for static initialization could be tricky. It seems that calling `Class.forName(driver)` should initialize and register the driver appropriately.\\\"}]}\"}, {\"type\": \"toolCall\", \"id\": \"call_RJa17QdwB4JG9mgTAfvf44SW|fc_07804db651c470730169fafaf01cc08193a8975196177b2c65\", \"name\": \"edit\", \"arguments\": {\"path\": \"tests/src/org.tpolecat/doobie-core_3/0.13.4/src/test/scala/org_tpolecat/doobie_core_3/TransactorInnerTransactorInnerFromDriverManagerTest.scala\", \"edits\": [{\"oldText\": \"import java.sql.SQLException\\nimport scala.concurrent.ExecutionContext\\n\\nclass TransactorInnerTransactorInnerFromDriverManagerTest {\\n  private implicit val contextShift: ContextShift[IO] = IO.contextShift(ExecutionContext.global)\\n  private val blocker: Blocker = Blocker.liftExecutionContext(ExecutionContext.global)\\n\\n  @Test\\n  @Timeout(10)\\n  def fromDriverManagerLoadsDriverClassWhenOpeningConnection(): Unit = {\\n    val xa: Transactor.Aux[IO, Unit] =\\n      Transactor.fromDriverManager[IO](\\n        \\\"java.lang.String\\\",\\n        \\\"jdbc:doobie-core-test:missing-database\\\",\\n        blocker\\n      )\\n\\n    val result: Either[Throwable, Unit] =\\n      xa.connect(xa.kernel).use(_ => IO.unit).attempt.unsafeRunSync()\\n\\n    val failure: Throwable =\\n      result.swap.getOrElse(new AssertionError(\\\"Expected connection acquisition to fail\\\"))\\n\\n    assertThat(failure).isInstanceOf(classOf[SQLException])\\n    assertThat(failure.getMessage).contains(\\\"No suitable driver\\\")\\n  }\\n}\\n\", \"newText\": \"import java.sql.Connection\\nimport java.sql.Driver\\nimport java.sql.DriverManager\\nimport java.sql.DriverPropertyInfo\\nimport java.sql.SQLException\\nimport java.util.Properties\\nimport java.util.logging.Logger\\nimport scala.concurrent.ExecutionContext\\n\\nclass TransactorInnerTransactorInnerFromDriverManagerTest {\\n  private implicit val contextShift: ContextShift[IO] = IO.contextShift(ExecutionContext.global)\\n  private val blocker: Blocker = Blocker.liftExecutionContext(ExecutionContext.global)\\n\\n  @Test\\n  @Timeout(10)\\n  def fromDriverManagerLoadsDriverClassWhenOpeningConnection(): Unit = {\\n    val driver: DoobieCoreFromDriverManagerFailingDriver = new DoobieCoreFromDriverManagerFailingDriver\\n    DriverManager.registerDriver(driver)\\n    try {\\n      val xa: Transactor.Aux[IO, Unit] =\\n        Transactor.fromDriverManager[IO](\\n          classOf[DoobieCoreFromDriverManagerFailingDriver].getName,\\n          DoobieCoreFromDriverManagerFailingDriver.url,\\n          blocker\\n        )\\n\\n      val result: Either[Throwable, Unit] =\\n        xa.connect(xa.kernel).use(_ => IO.unit).attempt.unsafeRunSync()\\n\\n      val failure: Throwable =\\n        result.swap.getOrElse(new AssertionError(\\\"Expected connection acquisition to fail\\\"))\\n\\n      assertThat(failure).isInstanceOf(classOf[SQLException])\\n      assertThat(failure.getMessage).contains(DoobieCoreFromDriverManagerFailingDriver.failureMessage)\\n    } finally {\\n      DriverManager.deregisterDriver(driver)\\n    }\\n  }\\n}\\n\\nobject DoobieCoreFromDriverManagerFailingDriver {\\n  val url: String = \\\"jdbc:doobie-core-from-driver-manager-test\\\"\\n  val failureMessage: String = \\\"driver was loaded and asked to connect\\\"\\n}\\n\\nclass DoobieCoreFromDriverManagerFailingDriver extends Driver {\\n  override def connect(url: String, info: Properties): Connection = {\\n    if (acceptsURL(url)) {\\n      throw new SQLException(DoobieCoreFromDriverManagerFailingDriver.failureMessage)\\n    }\\n    null\\n  }\\n\\n  override def acceptsURL(url: String): Boolean =\\n    DoobieCoreFromDriverManagerFailingDriver.url == url\\n\\n  override def getPropertyInfo(url: String, info: Properties): Array[DriverPropertyInfo] =\\n    Array.empty[DriverPropertyInfo]\\n\\n  override def getMajorVersion: Int = 1\\n\\n  override def getMinorVersion: Int = 0\\n\\n  override def jdbcCompliant(): Boolean = false\\n\\n  override def getParentLogger: Logger = Logger.getGlobal\\n}\\n\"}]}}], \"api\": \"openai-responses\", \"provider\": \"OCA\", \"model\": \"gpt-5.5\", \"usage\": {\"input\": 481, \"output\": 2170, \"cacheRead\": 21504, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"totalTokens\": 24155, \"cost\": {\"input\": 0, \"output\": 0, \"cacheRead\": 0, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"total\": 0}}, \"stopReason\": \"toolUse\", \"timestamp\": 1778055772822, \"responseId\": \"resp_07804db651c470730169fafa5ddd2c819399671712d99cc6c2\"}}\n1454:[tool-exec] start id=call_RJa17QdwB4JG9mgTAfvf44SW|fc_07804db651c470730169fafaf01cc08193a8975196177b2c65 name=edit args={\"path\": \"tests/src/org.tpolecat/doobie-core_3/0.13.4/src/test/scala/org_tpolecat/doobie_core_3/TransactorI